Did you know you can use essential oils to help naturally balance your hormones?⁠
⁠
Here are a few of the essential oils I recommend friends and family use ⬇️⁠

⁠
Thyme oil benefits the body by producing more progesterone, which helps balance the body’s hormones. ⁠
⁠
And, sandalwood oil helps balance testosterone levels in both men and women. ⁠
⁠
Want to learn more ways to naturally balance your hormones? Head over to my stories and swipe up.

node.text:
Getting enough protein is important for maintaining energy levels, building muscle, and supporting a healthy metabolism.⁠
⁠
And a lot of people following a plant-based diet struggle to find quality sources that don't upset the gut. ⁠
⁠
That's why Jordan Rubin and I formulated @ancientnutrition's Plant Protein+ to be a first-of-its-kind formula that's specifically intended to help support digestion, nutrient absorption and overall wellness.⁠
⁠
➡️ Flax, chia and hemp seeds are suppliers of omega-3s, watermelon seeds feature omega fatty acids, magnesium, zinc and potassium. ⁠
⁠
➡️ Ashwagandha root extract, ginseng and holy basil can help support a healthy response to stress, cognitive function, and more. ⁠
⁠
Head to my profile and click the link in my bio to learn more about @ancientnutrition's Plant Protein+.

node.text:
You'll love this apple cinnamon baked oatmeal recipe on a cool, fall morning. ⁠
⁠
The steel-cut oats give a hearty, chewy texture, and the cinnamon, nutmeg and cardamon add great flavor. ⁠
⁠
I like using steel-cut oats because they go through very little processing when compared to instant oats, are high in fiber so they keep you full longer, can help boost your immune system and reduce inflammation. ⁠
⁠
What you'll need for this recipe: ⁠
4 cups full-fat, canned coconut milk⁠
½ cup coconut sugar⁠
2 tablespoons butter⁠
¾ teaspoon cinnamon⁠
¼ teaspoon nutmeg⁠
⅛ teaspoon cardamom⁠
2 cups steel-cut oats⁠
2 cups chopped apples⁠
½ cup raisins⁠
1 cup chopped nuts⁠
½ teaspoon sea salt⁠
⁠
You can also add a scoop of @ancientnutrition's Bone Broth Protein Pure to get a giant boost in protein, hyaluronic acid, glucosamine, chondroitin and collagen. ⁠
Head to my profile and click the link in my bio for the full recipe.

Every morning, I start the day with a gratitude practice I like to call my "spiritual triathlons."⁠⁠
⁠⁠
This usually means that I wake up and spend the first few minutes of my day listing out everything that I'm grateful for. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Then, I'll read the bible or a personal growth book for 5 or 10 minutes. I finish up my triathlon by praying about or meditating on what I've read.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Since I began doing my morning triathlons, I've noticed small things that used to stress me out or slow me down have much less power in my daily life.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Do you have a morning ritual similar to my spiritual triathlon? ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Tell me about how you start your days in the comments, then head to my bio and click the link to learn more about how you can build your own morning ritual.
